4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, each county with a
6 population of 400,000 or more shall have a county
7 personnel board for all employees and appointees
8 holding positions in the classified service of the
9 county and each municipality with a population of 5,000
10 or more.
11 This bill would authorize a Class 8 municipality
12 with a population of 25,000 or more according to the
13 last decennial census and that has a corporate limit
14 lying in two counties to opt out of the county
15 personnel board's jurisdiction after six months notice,
16 and to opt back in to the jurisdiction of the county
17 personnel board not less than 10 years thereafter at
18 the sole discretion of the municipality.
19 This bill would require a municipality that opts
20 out of a county personnel board's jurisdiction to
21 create its own municipal civil service system and
22 continue all vested rights and interests of employees
23 and appointees who were subject to the county personnel
24 board.
25 This bill would prohibit a municipality subject
26 to this act from engaging in discrimination which is in
27 violation of federal or state law and would require the
28 municipality to adopt a certain antidiscrimination
Page 1

municipality to adopt a certain antidiscrimination
HB153 INTRODUCED
29 policy.
30 This bill would provide and confirm that the act
31 is intended to be retroactive and curative.
32 This bill would also repeal a law that
33 authorizes certain Class 8 municipalities to opt out of
34 a county personnel board.
35
36
37 A BILL
38 TO BE ENTITLED
39 AN ACT
40
41 Relating to county personnel boards; to add Section
42 11-43-5.3 to the Code of Alabama 1975, to authorize certain
43 municipalities to opt out from the jurisdiction of a county
44 personnel board and to require a municipality that opts out
45 from the jurisdiction of a county personnel board to create a
46 civil service system and continue the rights of employees and
47 officials vested or vesting in the county personnel board; to
48 repeal Section 11-43-5.2, Code of Alabama 1975, which
49 authorizes certain Class 8 municipalities to opt out of a
50 county personnel board; and to provide and confirm that the
51 act is retroactive and curative.
52 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
53 Section 1. Section 11-43-5.3 is added to the Code of
54 Alabama 1975, to read as follows:
55 §11-43-5.3
56 (a) This section shall apply to any Class 8
Page 2

(a) This section shall apply to any Class 8
HB153 INTRODUCED
57 municipality with a corporate limit lying in two counties,
58 which has a population equal to or greater than 25,000
59 according to the last decennial census and which was subject,
60 on January 1, 2023, to a county personnel board.
61 (b)(1) The governing body of a municipality, by
62 ordinance, may opt out from the jurisdiction of a county
63 personnel board, effective six months after the effective date
64 of the ordinance. A copy of the ordinance shall be transmitted
65 to the county personnel board following its passage by the
66 municipal governing body.
67 (2) Not less than 10 years after a municipality opts
68 out from the county personnel board's jurisdiction as provided
69 in subdivision (1), the municipality, by ordinance, may opt
70 back in to a county personnel board's jurisdiction, effective
71 six months after the effective date of the ordinance. A copy
72 of the ordinance shall be transmitted to the county personnel
73 board following its passage by the governing body.
74 (c) Any municipality that opts out from the county
75 personnel board's jurisdiction as provided in subdivision
76 (b)(1) shall create its own municipal civil service system
77 which shall ensure that the vested or vesting rights of any
78 existing appointees of the county civil service system are
79 protected and not otherwise altered or diminished, except as
80 otherwise provided for by law.
81 (d)(1) Any municipality exercising its rights under
82 this section may not engage in any type or form of
83 discrimination that is prohibited by federal or state law.
84 (2) Any municipality that elects to opt out as provided
Page 3

(2) Any municipality that elects to opt out as provided
HB153 INTRODUCED
85 in this section shall enact a policy that explicitly prohibits
86 the appointment, promotion, demotion, or dismissal of an
87 employee from any position which in any way favors or
88 discriminates against the employee because of his or her
89 political or religious opinions or affiliations or because of
90 his or her race or gender or for any other reason that is
91 prohibited by state or federal law.
92 Section 2. It is the intent of the Legislature that
93 this act be construed as retroactive and curative, and the
94 actions of any municipality that opted out from the county
95 personnel board's jurisdiction and created its own municipal
96 civil service system pursuant to Act 2023-460 of the 2023
97 Regular Session are hereby ratified, validated, approved, and
98 confirmed.
99 Section 3. Section 11-43-5.2, Code of Alabama 1975,
100 created by Act 2023-460 of the 2023 Regular Session and which
101 authorizes certain Class 8 municipalities to opt out of a
102 county personnel board and create its own municipal civil
103 service system, is repealed.
104 Section 4. This act shall become effective immediately.
